  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "For example, when analyzing a series of fossil images taken from various angles or at different stages of excavation, Transformers can effectively aggregate and interpret data from all images, offering a comprehensive view of the fossil's structure and features.",
    "Their self-attention mechanism enables the identification of intricate patterns and correlations across image sequences, which enhances the accuracy of fossil classification and analysis.",
    "Vision Transformers (ViTs) extend this capability to image-based tasks by applying Transformer architecture to image patches (Park and Kim 2022), as illustrated in Fig. 7.",
    "Instead of processing entire images directly, ViTs divide images into fixed-size patches, which are then linearly embedded and processed through the Transformer's self-attention layers (Raghu et al. 2021).",
    "The self-attention mechanism in ViTs allows the model to focus on relevant patches, capturing detailed spatial relationships within the image (Park and Kim 2022)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Vision Transformers (ViTs) extend this capability to image-based tasks by applying Transformer architecture to image patches (Park and Kim 2022), as illustrated in Fig. 7.",
    "Instead of processing entire images directly, ViTs divide images into fixed-size patches, which are then linearly embedded and processed through the Transformer's self-attention layers (Raghu et al. 2021).",
    "The self-attention mechanism in ViTs allows the model to focus on relevant patches, capturing detailed spatial relationships within the image (Park and Kim 2022)."
